text:
 Preparing the tofu and noodles Drain the tofu. Cut it into cubes about 1.5 centimeter (0.6 in) in size. Cook the noodles. Boil the water in a large saucepan. Add a pinch of salt. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/01\/Make-Green-Tea-Noodle-Soup-Step-2Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-Green-Tea-Noodle-Soup-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/01\/Make-Green-Tea-Noodle-Soup-Step-2Bullet1.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-Green-Tea-Noodle-Soup-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Add the noodles and cook for 5 minutes, or until tender. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d6\/Make-Green-Tea-Noodle-Soup-Step-2Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-Green-Tea-Noodle-Soup-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d6\/Make-Green-Tea-Noodle-Soup-Step-2Bullet2.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-Green-Tea-Noodle-Soup-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Drain when cooked. Rinse under cold water and set aside. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/89\/Make-Green-Tea-Noodle-Soup-Step-2Bullet3.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-Green-Tea-Noodle-Soup-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/89\/Make-Green-Tea-Noodle-Soup-Step-2Bullet3.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-Green-Tea-Noodle-Soup-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"} Preparing the soup base Pour 1.5 liters (0.4 US gal) of water into a large saucepan. Add the dashi granules. Heat the water over medium to high heat until the dashi granules dissolve. Then turn the heat up to high and bring to the boil. When boiling, add the mirin and soy sauce.  Assembling the soup Place even amounts of cooked noodles in four bowls. Add the tofu cubes in even amounts. Pour the hot soup stock over the noodles.  Garnish. Sprinkle each bowl with nor and toasted sesame seeds. Serve immediately.
